### Note on Google Sheets (Excel) organization:
To store the **Join our community** responses in a separate tab, update your Google Apps Script (`Code.gs`) to detect the `sheetName` property I've added to the JSON payload:

```javascript
function doPost(e) {
  var data = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);
  var ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();

  // Use the sheetName from the payload, or default to a sheet called "Submissions"
  var sheetName = data.sheetName || "Submissions";
  var sheet = ss.getSheetByName(sheetName);

  // If the sheet doesn't exist, create it
  if (!sheet) {
    sheet = ss.insertSheet(sheetName);
  }

  // Your logic to append data...
  sheet.appendRow([data.timestamp, data.firstName, data.lastName, ...]);

  return ContentService.createTextOutput("Success");
}
```

This way, the **Partners** form (which doesn't send a `sheetName` yet or sends a different one) will go to its own page, while **Community** and **Volunteer** will go to theirs.

