### 1. What to name the pages (Tabs) in the Excel/Sheet:
Create four separate tabs in your Google Sheet with these **exact** names:
1.  **`Community`**
2.  **`Volunteer`**
3.  **`Facilitators`**
4.  **`Partners`**

### 2. Do I need to edit the App Script for each page?
**No.** One script and one URL will work for all. 

You should update your existing Google Apps Script to look like this. It checks the `sheetName` property I've added to the code and automatically directs the data to the correct tab.

```javascript
function doPost(e) {
  try {
    var data = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);
    var ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();

    // 1. Get the sheet name from the app (Community, Volunteer, Facilitators, or Partners)
    // If no name is provided, it defaults to a sheet called "General"
    var sheetName = data.sheetName || "General";
    var sheet = ss.getSheetByName(sheetName);

    // 2. If the tab doesn't exist, create it automatically
    if (!sheet) {
      sheet = ss.insertSheet(sheetName);
    }

    // 3. Prepare the data row. 
    // You can customize this list based on what fields you want to see first.
    var row = [
      data.timestamp,
      data.source,
      data.fullName || (data.firstName + " " + data.lastName),
      data.email,
      data.phone || data.whatsapp || "N/A",
      data.location || data.country || "N/A",
      data.track || data.trackInterestedIn || data.department || "N/A",
      data.motivation || data.reason || "N/A",
      data.experience || "N/A"
    ];

    sheet.appendRow(row);

    return ContentService.createTextOutput("Success").setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.TEXT);

  } catch (error) {
    return ContentService.createTextOutput("Error: " + error.toString()).setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.TEXT);
  }
}
```

### How to Save & Update:
1. In your Google Sheet script editor, paste the code above.
2. Click **Deploy** > **New Deployment**.
3. Select **Web App**.
4. Set **Execute as:** `Me`.
5. Set **Who has access:** `Anyone`.
6. Click **Deploy** and copy the new **Web App URL**.
7. If the URL is different from the one currently in `CommunityOverlay.tsx` (ending in `/exec`), update that variable in the code.

Now, whenever a user clicks "**Finish & Submit**", the app sends the data along with the specific `sheetName`, and your script handles the filing!

